36enum client_hs_state_t {
37 state_read_hello_retry_request = 0,
38 state_send_second_client_hello,
39 state_read_server_hello,
40 state_read_encrypted_extensions,
41 state_read_certificate_request,
42 state_read_server_certificate,
43 state_read_server_certificate_verify,
44 state_server_certificate_reverify,
45 state_read_server_finished,
46 state_send_end_of_early_data,
47 state_send_client_encrypted_extensions,
48 state_send_client_certificate,
49 state_send_client_certificate_verify,
50 state_complete_second_flight,
51 state_done,
52};
53
54static const uint8_t kZeroes[EVP_MAX_MD_SIZE] = {0};
55
56// end_of_early_data closes the early data stream for |hs| and switches the
57// encryption level to |level|. It returns true on success and false on error.
58static bool close_early_data(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs, ssl_encryption_level_t level) {
59 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
60 assert(hs->in_early_data);
61
62 // Note |can_early_write| may already be false if |SSL_write| exceeded the
63 // early data write limit.
64 hs->can_early_write = false;
65
66 // 0-RTT write states on the client differ between TLS 1.3, DTLS 1.3, and
67 // QUIC. TLS 1.3 has one write encryption level at a time. 0-RTT write keys
68 // overwrite the null cipher and defer handshake write keys. While a
69 // HelloRetryRequest can cause us to rewind back to the null cipher, sequence
70 // numbers have no effect, so we can install a "new" null cipher.
71 //
72 // In QUIC and DTLS 1.3, 0-RTT write state cannot override or defer the normal
73 // write state. The two ClientHello sequence numbers must align, and handshake
74 // write keys must be installed early to ACK the EncryptedExtensions.
75 //
76 // We do not currently implement DTLS 1.3 and, in QUIC, the caller handles
77 // 0-RTT data, so we can skip installing 0-RTT keys and act as if there is one
78 // write level. If we implement DTLS 1.3, we'll need to model this better.
79 if (ssl->quic_method == nullptr) {
80 if (level == ssl_encryption_initial) {
81 bssl::UniquePtr<SSLAEADContext> null_ctx =
82 SSLAEADContext::CreateNullCipher(SSL_is_dtls(ssl));
83 if (!null_ctx ||
84 !ssl->method->set_write_state(ssl, ssl_encryption_initial,
85 std::move(null_ctx),
86 /*secret_for_quic=*/{})) {
87 return false;
88 }
89 ssl->s3->aead_write_ctx->SetVersionIfNullCipher(ssl->version);
90 } else {
91 assert(level == ssl_encryption_handshake);
92 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_seal,
93 hs->new_session.get(),
94 hs->client_handshake_secret())) {
95 return false;
96 }
97 }
98 }
99
100 assert(ssl->s3->write_level == level);
101 return true;
102}

104static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_hello_retry_request(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
105 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
106 assert(ssl->s3->have_version);
107 SSLMessage msg;
108 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
109 return ssl_hs_read_message;
110 }
111
112 // Queue up a ChangeCipherSpec for whenever we next send something. This
113 // will be before the second ClientHello. If we offered early data, this was
114 // already done.
115 if (!hs->early_data_offered &&
116 !ssl->method->add_change_cipher_spec(ssl)) {
117 return ssl_hs_error;
118 }
119
120 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO)) {
121 return ssl_hs_error;
122 }
123
124 CBS body = msg.body, extensions, server_random, session_id;
125 uint16_t server_version, cipher_suite;
126 uint8_t compression_method;
127 if (!CBS_get_u16(&body, &server_version) ||
128 !CBS_get_bytes(&body, &server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
129 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &session_id) ||
130 !CBS_mem_equal(&session_id, hs->session_id, hs->session_id_len) ||
131 !CBS_get_u16(&body, &cipher_suite) ||
132 !CBS_get_u8(&body, &compression_method) ||
133 compression_method != 0 ||
134 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
135 CBS_len(&extensions) == 0 ||
136 CBS_len(&body) != 0) {
137 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
138 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
139 return ssl_hs_error;
140 }
141
142 if (!CBS_mem_equal(&server_random, kHelloRetryRequest, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE)) {
143 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_hello;
144 return ssl_hs_ok;
145 }
146
147 const SSL_CIPHER *cipher = SSL_get_cipher_by_value(cipher_suite);
148 // Check if the cipher is a TLS 1.3 cipher.
149 if (cipher == NULL ||
150 SSL_CIPHER_get_min_version(cipher) > ssl_protocol_version(ssl) ||
151 SSL_CIPHER_get_max_version(cipher) < ssl_protocol_version(ssl)) {
152 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CIPHER_RETURNED);
153 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
154 return ssl_hs_error;
155 }
156
157 hs->new_cipher = cipher;
158
159 if (!hs->transcript.InitHash(ssl_protocol_version(ssl), hs->new_cipher) ||
160 !hs->transcript.UpdateForHelloRetryRequest()) {
161 return ssl_hs_error;
162 }
163
164
165 bool have_cookie, have_key_share, have_supported_versions;
166 CBS cookie, key_share, supported_versions;
167 SSL_EXTENSION_TYPE ext_types[] = {
168 {TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share, &have_key_share, &key_share},
169 {TLSEXT_TYPE_cookie, &have_cookie, &cookie},
170 {TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions, &have_supported_versions,
171 &supported_versions},
172 };
173
174 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
175 if (!ssl_parse_extensions(&extensions, &alert, ext_types,
176 /*ignore_unknown=*/false)) {
177 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
178 return ssl_hs_error;
179 }
180
181 if (!have_cookie && !have_key_share) {
182 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EMPTY_HELLO_RETRY_REQUEST);
183 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
184 return ssl_hs_error;
185 }
186 if (have_cookie) {
187 CBS cookie_value;
188 if (!CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&cookie, &cookie_value) ||
189 CBS_len(&cookie_value) == 0 ||
190 CBS_len(&cookie) != 0) {
191 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
192 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
193 return ssl_hs_error;
194 }
195
196 if (!hs->cookie.CopyFrom(cookie_value)) {
197 return ssl_hs_error;
198 }
199 }
200
201 if (have_key_share) {
202 uint16_t group_id;
203 if (!CBS_get_u16(&key_share, &group_id) || CBS_len(&key_share) != 0) {
204 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
205 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
206 return ssl_hs_error;
207 }
208
209 // The group must be supported.
210 if (!tls1_check_group_id(hs, group_id)) {
211 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
212 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CURVE);
213 return ssl_hs_error;
214 }
215
216 // Check that the HelloRetryRequest does not request a key share that was
217 // provided in the initial ClientHello.
218 if (hs->key_shares[0]->GroupID() == group_id ||
219 (hs->key_shares[1] && hs->key_shares[1]->GroupID() == group_id)) {
220 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
221 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CURVE);
222 return ssl_hs_error;
223 }
224
225 hs->key_shares[0].reset();
226 hs->key_shares[1].reset();
227 hs->retry_group = group_id;
228 }
229
230 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
231 return ssl_hs_error;
232 }
233
234 // HelloRetryRequest should be the end of the flight.
235 if (ssl->method->has_unprocessed_handshake_data(ssl)) {
236 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
237 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EXCESS_HANDSHAKE_DATA);
238 return ssl_hs_error;
239 }
240
241 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
242 ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request = true;
243 hs->tls13_state = state_send_second_client_hello;
244 // 0-RTT is rejected if we receive a HelloRetryRequest.
245 if (hs->in_early_data) {
246 ssl->s3->early_data_reason = ssl_early_data_hello_retry_request;
247 if (!close_early_data(hs, ssl_encryption_initial)) {
248 return ssl_hs_error;
249 }
250 return ssl_hs_early_data_rejected;
251 }
252 return ssl_hs_ok;
253}
254
255static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_second_client_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
256 // Any 0-RTT keys must have been discarded.
257 assert(hs->ssl->s3->write_level == ssl_encryption_initial);
258
259 if (!ssl_write_client_hello(hs)) {
260 return ssl_hs_error;
261 }
262
263 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_hello;
264 return ssl_hs_flush;
265}
266
267static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_server_hello(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
268 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
269 SSLMessage msg;
270 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
271 return ssl_hs_read_message;
272 }
273 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_SERVER_HELLO)) {
274 return ssl_hs_error;
275 }
276
277 CBS body = msg.body, server_random, session_id, extensions;
278 uint16_t server_version;
279 uint16_t cipher_suite;
280 uint8_t compression_method;
281 if (!CBS_get_u16(&body, &server_version) ||
282 !CBS_get_bytes(&body, &server_random, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE) ||
283 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &session_id) ||
284 !CBS_mem_equal(&session_id, hs->session_id, hs->session_id_len) ||
285 !CBS_get_u16(&body, &cipher_suite) ||
286 !CBS_get_u8(&body, &compression_method) ||
287 compression_method != 0 ||
288 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
289 CBS_len(&body) != 0) {
290 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
291 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
292 return ssl_hs_error;
293 }
294
295 if (server_version != TLS1_2_VERSION) {
296 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
297 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_VERSION_NUMBER);
298 return ssl_hs_error;
299 }
300
301 // Forbid a second HelloRetryRequest.
302 if (CBS_mem_equal(&server_random, kHelloRetryRequest, SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE)) {
303 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
304 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
305 return ssl_hs_error;
306 }
307
308 OPENSSL_memcpy(ssl->s3->server_random, CBS_data(&server_random),
309 SSL3_RANDOM_SIZE);
310
311 // Check if the cipher is a TLS 1.3 cipher.
312 const SSL_CIPHER *cipher = SSL_get_cipher_by_value(cipher_suite);
313 if (cipher == nullptr ||
314 SSL_CIPHER_get_min_version(cipher) > ssl_protocol_version(ssl) ||
315 SSL_CIPHER_get_max_version(cipher) < ssl_protocol_version(ssl)) {
316 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CIPHER_RETURNED);
317 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
318 return ssl_hs_error;
319 }
320
321 // Check that the cipher matches the one in the HelloRetryRequest.
322 if (ssl->s3->used_hello_retry_request && hs->new_cipher != cipher) {
323 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_WRONG_CIPHER_RETURNED);
324 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
325 return ssl_hs_error;
326 }
327
328 // Parse out the extensions.
329 bool have_key_share = false, have_pre_shared_key = false,
330 have_supported_versions = false;
331 CBS key_share, pre_shared_key, supported_versions;
332 SSL_EXTENSION_TYPE ext_types[] = {
333 {TLSEXT_TYPE_key_share, &have_key_share, &key_share},
334 {TLSEXT_TYPE_pre_shared_key, &have_pre_shared_key, &pre_shared_key},
335 {TLSEXT_TYPE_supported_versions, &have_supported_versions,
336 &supported_versions},
337 };
338
339 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
340 if (!ssl_parse_extensions(&extensions, &alert, ext_types,
341 /*ignore_unknown=*/false)) {
342 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
343 return ssl_hs_error;
344 }
345
346 // Recheck supported_versions, in case this is the second ServerHello.
347 uint16_t version;
348 if (!have_supported_versions ||
349 !CBS_get_u16(&supported_versions, &version) ||
350 version != ssl->version) {
351 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_SECOND_SERVERHELLO_VERSION_MISMATCH);
352 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
353 return ssl_hs_error;
354 }
355
356 alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
357 if (have_pre_shared_key) {
358 if (ssl->session == NULL) {
359 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION);
360 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNSUPPORTED_EXTENSION);
361 return ssl_hs_error;
362 }
363
364 if (!ssl_ext_pre_shared_key_parse_serverhello(hs, &alert,
365 &pre_shared_key)) {
366 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
367 return ssl_hs_error;
368 }
369
370 if (ssl->session->ssl_version != ssl->version) {
371 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_OLD_SESSION_VERSION_NOT_RETURNED);
372 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
373 return ssl_hs_error;
374 }
375
376 if (ssl->session->cipher->algorithm_prf != cipher->algorithm_prf) {
377 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_OLD_SESSION_PRF_HASH_MISMATCH);
378 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
379 return ssl_hs_error;
380 }
381
382 if (!ssl_session_is_context_valid(hs, ssl->session.get())) {
383 // This is actually a client application bug.
384 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL,
385 SSL_R_ATTEMPT_TO_REUSE_SESSION_IN_DIFFERENT_CONTEXT);
386 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
387 return ssl_hs_error;
388 }
389
390 ssl->s3->session_reused = true;
391 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
392 // Only authentication information carries over in TLS 1.3.
393 hs->new_session =
394 SSL_SESSION_dup(ssl->session.get(), SSL_SESSION_DUP_AUTH_ONLY);
395 if (!hs->new_session) {
396 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
397 return ssl_hs_error;
398 }
399 ssl_set_session(ssl, NULL);
400
401 // Resumption incorporates fresh key material, so refresh the timeout.
402 ssl_session_renew_timeout(ssl, hs->new_session.get(),
403 ssl->session_ctx->session_psk_dhe_timeout);
404 } else if (!ssl_get_new_session(hs)) {
405 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
406 return ssl_hs_error;
407 }
408
409 hs->new_session->cipher = cipher;
410 hs->new_cipher = cipher;
411
412 size_t hash_len =
413 EVP_MD_size(ssl_get_handshake_digest(ssl_protocol_version(ssl), cipher));
414
415 // Set up the key schedule and incorporate the PSK into the running secret.
416 if (ssl->s3->session_reused) {
417 if (!tls13_init_key_schedule(
418 hs, MakeConstSpan(hs->new_session->secret,
419 hs->new_session->secret_length))) {
420 return ssl_hs_error;
421 }
422 } else if (!tls13_init_key_schedule(hs, MakeConstSpan(kZeroes, hash_len))) {
423 return ssl_hs_error;
424 }
425
426 if (!have_key_share) {
427 // We do not support psk_ke and thus always require a key share.
428 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_MISSING_KEY_SHARE);
429 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_MISSING_EXTENSION);
430 return ssl_hs_error;
431 }
432
433 // Resolve ECDHE and incorporate it into the secret.
434 Array<uint8_t> dhe_secret;
435 alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
436 if (!ssl_ext_key_share_parse_serverhello(hs, &dhe_secret, &alert,
437 &key_share)) {
438 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
439 return ssl_hs_error;
440 }
441
442 if (!tls13_advance_key_schedule(hs, dhe_secret) ||
443 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg) ||
444 !tls13_derive_handshake_secrets(hs)) {
445 return ssl_hs_error;
446 }
447
448 // If currently sending early data over TCP, we defer installing client
449 // traffic keys to when the early data stream is closed. See
450 // |close_early_data|. Note if the server has already rejected 0-RTT via
451 // HelloRetryRequest, |in_early_data| is already false.
452 if (!hs->in_early_data || ssl->quic_method != nullptr) {
453 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_seal,
454 hs->new_session.get(),
455 hs->client_handshake_secret())) {
456 return ssl_hs_error;
457 }
458 }
459
460 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_handshake, evp_aead_open,
461 hs->new_session.get(),
462 hs->server_handshake_secret())) {
463 return ssl_hs_error;
464 }
465
466 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
467 hs->tls13_state = state_read_encrypted_extensions;
468 return ssl_hs_ok;
469}
470
471static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_encrypted_extensions(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
472 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
473 SSLMessage msg;
474 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
475 return ssl_hs_read_message;
476 }
477 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_ENCRYPTED_EXTENSIONS)) {
478 return ssl_hs_error;
479 }
480
481 CBS body = msg.body;
482 if (!ssl_parse_serverhello_tlsext(hs, &body)) {
483 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_PARSE_TLSEXT);
484 return ssl_hs_error;
485 }
486 if (CBS_len(&body) != 0) {
487 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
488 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
489 return ssl_hs_error;
490 }
491
492 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
493 if (hs->early_session->cipher != hs->new_session->cipher) {
494 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CIPHER_MISMATCH_ON_EARLY_DATA);
495 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
496 return ssl_hs_error;
497 }
498 if (MakeConstSpan(hs->early_session->early_alpn) !=
499 ssl->s3->alpn_selected) {
500 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_ALPN_MISMATCH_ON_EARLY_DATA);
501 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
502 return ssl_hs_error;
503 }
504 // Channel ID and Token Binding are incompatible with 0-RTT. The ALPS
505 // extension should be negotiated implicitly.
506 if (ssl->s3->channel_id_valid || ssl->s3->token_binding_negotiated ||
507 hs->new_session->has_application_settings) {
508 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_UNEXPECTED_EXTENSION_ON_EARLY_DATA);
509 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
510 return ssl_hs_error;
511 }
512 hs->new_session->has_application_settings =
513 hs->early_session->has_application_settings;
514 if (!hs->new_session->local_application_settings.CopyFrom(
515 hs->early_session->local_application_settings) ||
516 !hs->new_session->peer_application_settings.CopyFrom(
517 hs->early_session->peer_application_settings)) {
518 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
519 return ssl_hs_error;
520 }
521 }
522
523 // Store the negotiated ALPN in the session.
524 if (!hs->new_session->early_alpn.CopyFrom(ssl->s3->alpn_selected)) {
525 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
526 return ssl_hs_error;
527 }
528
529 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
530 return ssl_hs_error;
531 }
532
533 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
534 hs->tls13_state = state_read_certificate_request;
535 if (hs->in_early_data && !ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
536 if (!close_early_data(hs, ssl_encryption_handshake)) {
537 return ssl_hs_error;
538 }
539 return ssl_hs_early_data_rejected;
540 }
541 return ssl_hs_ok;
542}

544static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_certificate_request(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
545 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
546 // CertificateRequest may only be sent in non-resumption handshakes.
547 if (ssl->s3->session_reused) {
548 if (ssl->ctx->reverify_on_resume && !ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
549 hs->tls13_state = state_server_certificate_reverify;
550 return ssl_hs_ok;
551 }
552 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_finished;
553 return ssl_hs_ok;
554 }
555
556 SSLMessage msg;
557 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
558 return ssl_hs_read_message;
559 }
560
561 // CertificateRequest is optional.
562 if (msg.type != SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_REQUEST) {
563 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_certificate;
564 return ssl_hs_ok;
565 }
566
567
568 bool have_sigalgs = false, have_ca = false;
569 CBS sigalgs, ca;
570 const SSL_EXTENSION_TYPE ext_types[] = {
571 {TLSEXT_TYPE_signature_algorithms, &have_sigalgs, &sigalgs},
572 {TLSEXT_TYPE_certificate_authorities, &have_ca, &ca},
573 };
574
575 CBS body = msg.body, context, extensions, supported_signature_algorithms;
576 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
577 if (!CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(&body, &context) ||
578 // The request context is always empty during the handshake.
579 CBS_len(&context) != 0 ||
580 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
581 CBS_len(&body) != 0 ||
582 !ssl_parse_extensions(&extensions, &alert, ext_types,
583 /*ignore_unknown=*/true) ||
584 (have_ca && CBS_len(&ca) == 0) ||
585 !have_sigalgs ||
586 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(&sigalgs,
587 &supported_signature_algorithms) ||
588 !tls1_parse_peer_sigalgs(hs, &supported_signature_algorithms)) {
589 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
590 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
591 return ssl_hs_error;
592 }
593
594 if (have_ca) {
595 hs->ca_names = ssl_parse_client_CA_list(ssl, &alert, &ca);
596 if (!hs->ca_names) {
597 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
598 return ssl_hs_error;
599 }
600 } else {
601 hs->ca_names.reset(sk_CRYPTO_BUFFER_new_null());
602 if (!hs->ca_names) {
603 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, ERR_R_MALLOC_FAILURE);
604 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
605 return ssl_hs_error;
606 }
607 }
608
609 hs->cert_request = true;
610 ssl->ctx->x509_method->hs_flush_cached_ca_names(hs);
611
612 if (!ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
613 return ssl_hs_error;
614 }
615
616 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
617 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_certificate;
618 return ssl_hs_ok;
619}
620
621static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_server_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
622 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
623 SSLMessage msg;
624 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
625 return ssl_hs_read_message;
626 }
627
628 if (msg.type != SSL3_MT_COMPRESSED_CERTIFICATE &&
629 !ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE)) {
630 return ssl_hs_error;
631 }
632
633 if (!tls13_process_certificate(hs, msg, false /* certificate required */) ||
634 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
635 return ssl_hs_error;
636 }
637
638 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
639 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_certificate_verify;
640 return ssl_hs_ok;
641}
642
643static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_server_certificate_verify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
644 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
645 SSLMessage msg;
646 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
647 return ssl_hs_read_message;
648 }
649 switch (ssl_verify_peer_cert(hs)) {
650 case ssl_verify_ok:
651 break;
652 case ssl_verify_invalid:
653 return ssl_hs_error;
654 case ssl_verify_retry:
655 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_certificate_verify;
656 return ssl_hs_certificate_verify;
657 }
658
659 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_CERTIFICATE_VERIFY) ||
660 !tls13_process_certificate_verify(hs, msg) ||
661 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg)) {
662 return ssl_hs_error;
663 }
664
665 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
666 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_finished;
667 return ssl_hs_ok;
668}
669
670static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_server_certificate_reverify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
671 switch (ssl_reverify_peer_cert(hs, /*send_alert=*/true)) {
672 case ssl_verify_ok:
673 break;
674 case ssl_verify_invalid:
675 return ssl_hs_error;
676 case ssl_verify_retry:
677 hs->tls13_state = state_server_certificate_reverify;
678 return ssl_hs_certificate_verify;
679 }
680 hs->tls13_state = state_read_server_finished;
681 return ssl_hs_ok;
682}
683
684static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_read_server_finished(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
685 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
686 SSLMessage msg;
687 if (!ssl->method->get_message(ssl, &msg)) {
688 return ssl_hs_read_message;
689 }
690 if (!ssl_check_message_type(ssl, msg, SSL3_MT_FINISHED) ||
691 !tls13_process_finished(hs, msg, false /* don't use saved value */) ||
692 !ssl_hash_message(hs, msg) ||
693 // Update the secret to the master secret and derive traffic keys.
694 !tls13_advance_key_schedule(
695 hs, MakeConstSpan(kZeroes, hs->transcript.DigestLen())) ||
696 !tls13_derive_application_secrets(hs)) {
697 return ssl_hs_error;
698 }
699
700 // Finished should be the end of the flight.
701 if (ssl->method->has_unprocessed_handshake_data(ssl)) {
702 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_UNEXPECTED_MESSAGE);
703 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_EXCESS_HANDSHAKE_DATA);
704 return ssl_hs_error;
705 }
706
707 ssl->method->next_message(ssl);
708 hs->tls13_state = state_send_end_of_early_data;
709 return ssl_hs_ok;
710}
711
712static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_end_of_early_data(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
713 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
714
715 if (ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
716 // QUIC omits the EndOfEarlyData message. See draft-ietf-quic-tls-22,
717 // section 8.3.
718 if (ssl->quic_method == nullptr) {
719 ScopedCBB cbb;
720 CBB body;
721 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
722 SSL3_MT_END_OF_EARLY_DATA) ||
723 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
724 return ssl_hs_error;
725 }
726 }
727
728 if (!close_early_data(hs, ssl_encryption_handshake)) {
729 return ssl_hs_error;
730 }
731 }
732
733 hs->tls13_state = state_send_client_encrypted_extensions;
734 return ssl_hs_ok;
735}
736
737static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_client_encrypted_extensions(
738 SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
739 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
740 // For now, only one extension uses client EncryptedExtensions. This function
741 // may be generalized if others use it in the future.
742 if (hs->new_session->has_application_settings &&
743 !ssl->s3->early_data_accepted) {
744 ScopedCBB cbb;
745 CBB body, extensions, extension;
746 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body,
747 SSL3_MT_ENCRYPTED_EXTENSIONS) ||
748 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&body, &extensions) ||
749 !CBB_add_u16(&extensions, TLSEXT_TYPE_application_settings) ||
750 !CBB_add_u16_length_prefixed(&extensions, &extension) ||
751 !CBB_add_bytes(&extension,
752 hs->new_session->local_application_settings.data(),
753 hs->new_session->local_application_settings.size()) ||
754 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
755 return ssl_hs_error;
756 }
757 }
758
759 hs->tls13_state = state_send_client_certificate;
760 return ssl_hs_ok;
761}
762
763static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_client_certificate(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
764 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
765
766 // The peer didn't request a certificate.
767 if (!hs->cert_request) {
768 hs->tls13_state = state_complete_second_flight;
769 return ssl_hs_ok;
770 }
771
772 // Call cert_cb to update the certificate.
773 if (hs->config->cert->cert_cb != NULL) {
774 int rv = hs->config->cert->cert_cb(ssl, hs->config->cert->cert_cb_arg);
775 if (rv == 0) {
776 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_INTERNAL_ERROR);
777 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_CERT_CB_ERROR);
778 return ssl_hs_error;
779 }
780 if (rv < 0) {
781 hs->tls13_state = state_send_client_certificate;
782 return ssl_hs_x509_lookup;
783 }
784 }
785
786 if (!ssl_on_certificate_selected(hs) ||
787 !tls13_add_certificate(hs)) {
788 return ssl_hs_error;
789 }
790
791 hs->tls13_state = state_send_client_certificate_verify;
792 return ssl_hs_ok;
793}
794
795static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_send_client_certificate_verify(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
796 // Don't send CertificateVerify if there is no certificate.
797 if (!ssl_has_certificate(hs)) {
798 hs->tls13_state = state_complete_second_flight;
799 return ssl_hs_ok;
800 }
801
802 switch (tls13_add_certificate_verify(hs)) {
803 case ssl_private_key_success:
804 hs->tls13_state = state_complete_second_flight;
805 return ssl_hs_ok;
806
807 case ssl_private_key_retry:
808 hs->tls13_state = state_send_client_certificate_verify;
809 return ssl_hs_private_key_operation;
810
811 case ssl_private_key_failure:
812 return ssl_hs_error;
813 }
814
815 assert(0);
816 return ssl_hs_error;
817}
818
819static enum ssl_hs_wait_t do_complete_second_flight(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
820 SSL *const ssl = hs->ssl;
821 hs->can_release_private_key = true;
822
823 // Send a Channel ID assertion if necessary.
824 if (ssl->s3->channel_id_valid) {
825 if (!ssl_do_channel_id_callback(hs)) {
826 hs->tls13_state = state_complete_second_flight;
827 return ssl_hs_error;
828 }
829
830 if (hs->config->channel_id_private == NULL) {
831 return ssl_hs_channel_id_lookup;
832 }
833
834 ScopedCBB cbb;
835 CBB body;
836 if (!ssl->method->init_message(ssl, cbb.get(), &body, SSL3_MT_CHANNEL_ID) ||
837 !tls1_write_channel_id(hs, &body) ||
838 !ssl_add_message_cbb(ssl, cbb.get())) {
839 return ssl_hs_error;
840 }
841 }
842
843 // Send a Finished message.
844 if (!tls13_add_finished(hs)) {
845 return ssl_hs_error;
846 }
847
848 // Derive the final keys and enable them.
849 if (!tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_application, evp_aead_seal,
850 hs->new_session.get(),
851 hs->client_traffic_secret_0()) ||
852 !tls13_set_traffic_key(ssl, ssl_encryption_application, evp_aead_open,
853 hs->new_session.get(),
854 hs->server_traffic_secret_0()) ||
855 !tls13_derive_resumption_secret(hs)) {
856 return ssl_hs_error;
857 }
858
859 hs->tls13_state = state_done;
860 return ssl_hs_flush;
861}
862
863enum ssl_hs_wait_t tls13_client_handshake(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
864 while (hs->tls13_state != state_done) {
865 enum ssl_hs_wait_t ret = ssl_hs_error;
866 enum client_hs_state_t state =
867 static_cast<enum client_hs_state_t>(hs->tls13_state);
868 switch (state) {
869 case state_read_hello_retry_request:
870 ret = do_read_hello_retry_request(hs);
871 break;
872 case state_send_second_client_hello:
873 ret = do_send_second_client_hello(hs);
874 break;
875 case state_read_server_hello:
876 ret = do_read_server_hello(hs);
877 break;
878 case state_read_encrypted_extensions:
879 ret = do_read_encrypted_extensions(hs);
880 break;
881 case state_read_certificate_request:
882 ret = do_read_certificate_request(hs);
883 break;
884 case state_read_server_certificate:
885 ret = do_read_server_certificate(hs);
886 break;
887 case state_read_server_certificate_verify:
888 ret = do_read_server_certificate_verify(hs);
889 break;
890 case state_server_certificate_reverify:
891 ret = do_server_certificate_reverify(hs);
892 break;
893 case state_read_server_finished:
894 ret = do_read_server_finished(hs);
895 break;
896 case state_send_end_of_early_data:
897 ret = do_send_end_of_early_data(hs);
898 break;
899 case state_send_client_certificate:
900 ret = do_send_client_certificate(hs);
901 break;
902 case state_send_client_encrypted_extensions:
903 ret = do_send_client_encrypted_extensions(hs);
904 break;
905 case state_send_client_certificate_verify:
906 ret = do_send_client_certificate_verify(hs);
907 break;
908 case state_complete_second_flight:
909 ret = do_complete_second_flight(hs);
910 break;
911 case state_done:
912 ret = ssl_hs_ok;
913 break;
914 }
915
916 if (hs->tls13_state != state) {
917 ssl_do_info_callback(hs->ssl, SSL_CB_CONNECT_LOOP, 1);
918 }
919
920 if (ret != ssl_hs_ok) {
921 return ret;
922 }
923 }
924
925 return ssl_hs_ok;
926}
927
928const char *tls13_client_handshake_state(SSL_HANDSHAKE *hs) {
929 enum client_hs_state_t state =
930 static_cast<enum client_hs_state_t>(hs->tls13_state);
931 switch (state) {
932 case state_read_hello_retry_request:
933 return "TLS 1.3 client read_hello_retry_request";
934 case state_send_second_client_hello:
935 return "TLS 1.3 client send_second_client_hello";
936 case state_read_server_hello:
937 return "TLS 1.3 client read_server_hello";
938 case state_read_encrypted_extensions:
939 return "TLS 1.3 client read_encrypted_extensions";
940 case state_read_certificate_request:
941 return "TLS 1.3 client read_certificate_request";
942 case state_read_server_certificate:
943 return "TLS 1.3 client read_server_certificate";
944 case state_read_server_certificate_verify:
945 return "TLS 1.3 client read_server_certificate_verify";
946 case state_server_certificate_reverify:
947 return "TLS 1.3 client server_certificate_reverify";
948 case state_read_server_finished:
949 return "TLS 1.3 client read_server_finished";
950 case state_send_end_of_early_data:
951 return "TLS 1.3 client send_end_of_early_data";
952 case state_send_client_encrypted_extensions:
953 return "TLS 1.3 client send_client_encrypted_extensions";
954 case state_send_client_certificate:
955 return "TLS 1.3 client send_client_certificate";
956 case state_send_client_certificate_verify:
957 return "TLS 1.3 client send_client_certificate_verify";
958 case state_complete_second_flight:
959 return "TLS 1.3 client complete_second_flight";
960 case state_done:
961 return "TLS 1.3 client done";
962 }
963
964 return "TLS 1.3 client unknown";
965}
966
967bool tls13_process_new_session_ticket(SSL *ssl, const SSLMessage &msg) {
968 if (ssl->s3->write_shutdown != ssl_shutdown_none) {
969 // Ignore tickets on shutdown. Callers tend to indiscriminately call
970 // |SSL_shutdown| before destroying an |SSL|, at which point calling the new
971 // session callback may be confusing.
972 return true;
973 }
974
975 CBS body = msg.body;
976 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session = tls13_create_session_with_ticket(ssl, &body);
977 if (!session) {
978 return false;
979 }
980
981 if ((ssl->session_ctx->session_cache_mode & SSL_SESS_CACHE_CLIENT) &&
982 ssl->session_ctx->new_session_cb != NULL &&
983 ssl->session_ctx->new_session_cb(ssl, session.get())) {
984 // |new_session_cb|'s return value signals that it took ownership.
985 session.release();
986 }
987
988 return true;
989}
990
991UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> tls13_create_session_with_ticket(SSL *ssl, CBS *body) {
992 UniquePtr<SSL_SESSION> session = SSL_SESSION_dup(
993 ssl->s3->established_session.get(), SSL_SESSION_INCLUDE_NONAUTH);
994 if (!session) {
995 return nullptr;
996 }
997
998 ssl_session_rebase_time(ssl, session.get());
999
1000 uint32_t server_timeout;
1001 CBS ticket_nonce, ticket, extensions;
1002 if (!CBS_get_u32(body, &server_timeout) ||
1003 !CBS_get_u32(body, &session->ticket_age_add) ||
1004 !CBS_get_u8_length_prefixed(body, &ticket_nonce) ||
1005 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(body, &ticket) ||
1006 !session->ticket.CopyFrom(ticket) ||
1007 !CBS_get_u16_length_prefixed(body, &extensions) ||
1008 CBS_len(body) != 0) {
1009 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1010 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1011 return nullptr;
1012 }
1013
1014 // Cap the renewable lifetime by the server advertised value. This avoids
1015 // wasting bandwidth on 0-RTT when we know the server will reject it.
1016 if (session->timeout > server_timeout) {
1017 session->timeout = server_timeout;
1018 }
1019
1020 if (!tls13_derive_session_psk(session.get(), ticket_nonce)) {
1021 return nullptr;
1022 }
1023
1024 // Parse out the extensions.
1025 bool have_early_data = false;
1026 CBS early_data;
1027 const SSL_EXTENSION_TYPE ext_types[] = {
1028 {TLSEXT_TYPE_early_data, &have_early_data, &early_data},
1029 };
1030
1031 uint8_t alert = SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR;
1032 if (!ssl_parse_extensions(&extensions, &alert, ext_types,
1033 /*ignore_unknown=*/true)) {
1034 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, alert);
1035 return nullptr;
1036 }
1037
1038 if (have_early_data) {
1039 if (!CBS_get_u32(&early_data, &session->ticket_max_early_data) ||
1040 CBS_len(&early_data) != 0) {
1041 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_DECODE_ERROR);
1042 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1043 return nullptr;
1044 }
1045
1046 // QUIC does not use the max_early_data_size parameter and always sets it to
1047 // a fixed value. See draft-ietf-quic-tls-22, section 4.5.
1048 if (ssl->quic_method != nullptr &&
1049 session->ticket_max_early_data != 0xffffffff) {
1050 ssl_send_alert(ssl, SSL3_AL_FATAL, SSL_AD_ILLEGAL_PARAMETER);
1051 OPENSSL_PUT_ERROR(SSL, SSL_R_DECODE_ERROR);
1052 return nullptr;
1053 }
1054 }
1055
1056 // Historically, OpenSSL filled in fake session IDs for ticket-based sessions.
1057 // TODO(davidben): Are external callers relying on this? Try removing this.
1058 SHA256(CBS_data(&ticket), CBS_len(&ticket), session->session_id);
1059 session->session_id_length = SHA256_DIGEST_LENGTH;
1060
1061 session->ticket_age_add_valid = true;
1062 session->not_resumable = false;
1063
1064 return session;
1065}
